+      # Non-error audit event: a tmux-launched Claude phase reached the
+      # wait deadline WITHOUT the Stop-hook completion sentinel (`.done` /
+      # `result.json`) ever appearing, but a caller-supplied completion
+      # predicate proved the work actually completed (idle prompt observed,
+      # required artifacts present, commit/no-change evidence). Severity is
+      # conveyed by the event_type name itself — `Events#emit` has no
+      # separate `level` field, so WARN/non-error semantics live in the
+      # `claude_completion_fallback` name. The stage proceeds to SUCCESS;
+      # no new terminal marker is written. See
